			</p> <p><strong>Assigned To:</strong> Teko Bailey, Shuhratjon Nigmatov, Norton Lages, Nadine Karam, Karina Ricca, Johnson Mathews, Janet Teresa, German Ricca, Elie Karam</p> <p><strong>Assigned By:</strong> Edie Ross</p> <p><strong>View Task:</strong> <a style="color:#346CC4;" href="https://gprocommission2020.teamwork.com/tasks/7836745#comment3065486">How to deal with with duplicate accounts</a></p> <p><strong>Task List:</strong> <a style="color:#346CC4;" href="https://gprocommission2020.teamwork.com/tasklists/785930">General tasks</a></p> <p><strong>Task Description:</strong><br /><br /></p><p>Hello all - in the CRM it is possible to have duplicate accounts when someone registered with GProConneXt.com using a different email than we had for them in our CRM excel spreadsheets. </p>
<p>(For example, if I registered with GProConnext.com using edie@rreach.org and had edie@gprocommission.org listed as my email in our CRM spreadsheets, then I would have two accounts in the CRM.</p>
<p>The GProConneXt.com account would not have my CRM info (who I\'m assigned to, how often I\'d like to be contacted and what method, etc.) and the CRM account would not have the GProConnext.com info.</p>
<p>In this case - we need to take the following steps: </p>
<ol><li><p>We need to keep the account created through GProConneXt.com because this way the person is able to update their goals and actuals on GProConnext.com. Therefore, the GProcentral colleague to whom the contact is assigned will need to copy and paste the CRM info into the GProConnext.com account and make sure to assign that account to yourself. </p>
</li>
<li><p>Next the GProCentral Colleague adds the account that needs to be deleted to this sheet (below), identifying it by contact\'s name and the date it was created. Our IT team will delete these accounts on a monthly basis.</p>
</li>
</ol><p><a href="http://bit.ly/gprodelete" title="">http://bit.ly/gprodelete</a></p>
